The paper deals with the problem of estimating underlying comparison probabilities from pairwise comparison data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also discusses the use of stochastic transitivity and noisy sorting models, which are commonly used in ranking and preference elicitation tasks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
